post.description:
Creates a new autoload profile.
It requires a name, amount to load, frequency (daily, weekly, monthly), start date, and can optionally take an end date.
To load on the last day of the month, set specialCases to 'last_of_month'.

get.description: Gets an autoload profile by ID. The response includes the autoload profile and an array of cards associated with the autoload. The card array has three fields "cardId", "card" object, and "addedOn" referring to the date that card was added to the autoload.

patch.description:
Modifies an autoload profile. Modifications can optionally be made to the amount, name, frequency of the autoload (daily, weekly, monthly), status (active or ended), start and end dates. Returns the modified autoload profile.
Modifications to a date must be in the format YYYY-MM-DD
If you intend to change the frequency of the load or special case (load on the last day of the month), please pass the date you'd like the first load to occur on as startDate.
If you intend to switch from a set end date to indefinite, please set clearEndDate to true.
If you intend to cancel the autoload and immediately stop loads, set status to 'ended'.

post.description: Adds card(s) to an autoload. Added cards will be loaded on the date and with the amount set in the specified autoload profile. To create an autoload profile, refer to Create Autoload Profile.

delete.description: Removes card(s) from an autoload. If the autoload profile or any card ID is not found, this returns a 404 Not Found status.

Creates a recipient entity, representing a real person who will receive transfers. You can attach bank accounts to a recipient using the 'Add Bank Account to Recipient' endpoint if you have the account details or by collecting them through GiveCard Intake.
To request a recipient's bank details, set 'email' as the IntakeDeliveryType. The intake process also verifies the bank account details are valid. Once the account information is collected and verified, you can initiate transfers to the recipient.

For Virtual Cards, the Billing Address defaults to 123 GiveCard Way, New York, NY 10023 unless one is given.

This should only be chosen to eliminate the shipping time of receiving a new card, otherwise see Reissue Card.

post.description:
Reissuing a physical card should be used in cases of fraud or a lost card. This closes the cardholder's current card, issues, and ships them a card with new card details, expiration, last4, and pin.
The card ID and external ID will not change, funds will stay in the cardholder's account and do not need to be transferred to the new card, and the new card will automatically be linked to the cardholder's GiveCard platform account.

parameters.description: Either a card's ID or external ID acceptable.

post.description:
Reissuing a virtual card should be used in cases of fraud or a lost card. This closes the cardholder's current card and issues them a card with new card details, expiration, last4, and pin.
The card ID and external ID will not change, funds will stay in the cardholder's account and do not need to be transferred to the new card, and the new card will automatically appear in the cardholder's GiveCard platform account.

applyTo.x-go-enum-desc:
business ApplySpendRuleToBusiness  Apply to 'business' will apply the rule to all cards within the superbusiness or business.
program ApplySpendRuleToProgram  Apply to 'program' will apply the rule to all cards within a program. In cases of conflict with a business-applied rule, the program-applied rule will trump.
cards ApplySpendRuleToCards  Apply to 'cards' is a rule you *can* apply to any of your cards. It will not be automatically applied to any cards. In cases of conflict with a business or program-applied rule, the applied to card rule will trump.

UPS_SECOND_DAY ShipmentMethodSecondDay  Charges vary for "UPS_SECOND_DAY" and will be billed to your business

card FundingAccountTypeCard  Funding Account Types

applyTo.x-go-enum-desc:
business ApplySpendRuleToBusiness  Apply to 'business' will apply the rule to all cards within the superbusiness or business.
program ApplySpendRuleToProgram  Apply to 'program' will apply the rule to all cards within a program. In cases of conflict with a business-applied rule, the program-applied rule will trump.
cards ApplySpendRuleToCards  Apply to 'cards' is a rule you *can* apply to any of your cards. It will not be automatically applied to any cards. In cases of conflict with a business or program-applied rule, the applied to card rule will trump.

USPS_PRIORITY ShipmentMethodPriority  "USPS_PRIORITY" is the recommended shipment method. GiveCard covers the shipping cost for this shipment method.
UPS_NEXT_DAY ShipmentMethodNextDay  Charges vary for "UPS_NEXT_DAY" and will be billed to your business
UPS_SECOND_DAY ShipmentMethodSecondDay  Charges vary for "UPS_SECOND_DAY" and will be billed to your business

line1.description: Line1 replaces the business name on the front of the card. This should only be done with permission from GiveCard. It takes a maximum of 23 chars.

line2.description: Line2 replaces the externalId printed on the back of the card. This can have large support implications and should only be done with permission from GiveCard. It takes a maximum of 23 chars.

applyTo.x-go-enum-desc:
business ApplySpendRuleToBusiness  Apply to 'business' will apply the rule to all cards within the superbusiness or business.
program ApplySpendRuleToProgram  Apply to 'program' will apply the rule to all cards within a program. In cases of conflict with a business-applied rule, the program-applied rule will trump.
cards ApplySpendRuleToCards  Apply to 'cards' is a rule you *can* apply to any of your cards. It will not be automatically applied to any cards. In cases of conflict with a business or program-applied rule, the applied to card rule will trump.

description.description: Plain-english description of what the spend rule restricts. This will be surfaced to cardholders to give them an understanding of the restrictions on their card.

emailAddress.description: The email address to which the card will be tokenized to and accessed with for a digital wallet. This is required if the delivery method is "email."

expirationDate.description: The expiration date for the card. Default is 4 years from the current timestamp. Upon the expiration date, the card will be automatically closed. Note that once the card is closed on the expiration date, this is irreversible. Format is timestamp 2006-01-02T15:04:05Z.

merchantRuleId.description: Deprecated. Please use the spend rule IDs field instead.

phoneNumber.description: The phone number to which the card will be tokenized to and accessed with for a digital wallet. Must be 10 digits with no special characters.

spendRuleIds.description: Passing in a spend rule ID(s) applies spend rule(s) to a card upon order. To create a spend rule and limit where cardholders can use funds, refer to Create Spend Rule.

async.description: Set async to true to process loads asynchronously

LocalizedMessage.description:
Provides a localized error message that is safe to return to the user
which can be attached to an RPC error.

locale.description:
The locale used following the specification defined at
http://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/bcp/bcp47.txt.
Examples are: "en-US", "fr-CH", "es-MX"

message.description: The localized error message in the above locale.

ShippingAddressRequest.title: Mailing address where the card(s) will be sent. Cards arrive in 5-7 business days. Special characters and P.O. boxes are not permitted and will return a 400 Bad Request error.

applyTo.x-go-enum-desc:
business ApplySpendRuleToBusiness  Apply to 'business' will apply the rule to all cards within the superbusiness or business.
program ApplySpendRuleToProgram  Apply to 'program' will apply the rule to all cards within a program. In cases of conflict with a business-applied rule, the program-applied rule will trump.
cards ApplySpendRuleToCards  Apply to 'cards' is a rule you *can* apply to any of your cards. It will not be automatically applied to any cards. In cases of conflict with a business or program-applied rule, the applied to card rule will trump.

applyTo.x-go-enum-desc:
business ApplySpendRuleToBusiness  Apply to 'business' will apply the rule to all cards within the superbusiness or business.
program ApplySpendRuleToProgram  Apply to 'program' will apply the rule to all cards within a program. In cases of conflict with a business-applied rule, the program-applied rule will trump.
cards ApplySpendRuleToCards  Apply to 'cards' is a rule you *can* apply to any of your cards. It will not be automatically applied to any cards. In cases of conflict with a business or program-applied rule, the applied to card rule will trump.
